         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Au[s…] ¶ 14th Octer [1]896. ¶ Sir John Forrest KCMG etc etc ¶ Premier ¶ Perth...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.10.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">R. Pries to John Forrest</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Acc. 527, no. 3230/96, <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Colonial Secretary's Office — Correspondence</seg>, State Record Office of Western Australia, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">is this correct??</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Au[s…]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Looks to be damaged on MS.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14th Octer [1]896.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir John Forrest KCMG etc etc</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Premier</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Perth</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir John.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust you will pardon me if I venture to address you in correspondence of the sad news just received, of the death of Baron Sir F. von Mueller and mention one or two circumstances that possibly may not be known to you although I am well aware of the great friendship that existed between the late Baron &amp; yourself. As is well known he was born in Rostock, also my native town, was one of a family of nine brothers &amp; sisters all of whom died with the exception of one sister, widow of the late Doctor Weikl<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">sic.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> residing (i.e. about two years ago) in or near the Northern part of the town of Adelaide South Australia. The late Baron sometimes wrote of her and asked me for Rostock newspapers for her but from various remarks I drew the conclusion (possibly however an erroneous one) that she was in straightened circumstances and greatly dependent on her bother's assistance. If this should prove to be so I think you will agree with me that the sister of such a man should not be allowed to want. — All the Australian Colonies should I think bear the burden of her maintenance in ease and comforts. —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Excuse the liberty I have taken and believe me</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir John</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedt Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R F Pries<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also [Under Secretary] to R. Pries, 20 October 1896.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
